<div class="settings-section-heading">
  <span class="settings-section-icon"><i class="fa fa-cloud"></i></span>
  <div>
    <h2>Bluesky handle</h2>
    <p>Verify this Neocities site and use its domain as your handle on <a href="https://bsky.app/">Bluesky</a>.</p>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="settings-handle-card">
  <span class="settings-handle-at">@</span>
  <div><span class="settings-kicker">Your domain handle</span><strong><%= @site.host %></strong></div>
</div>

<ol class="settings-instruction-list">
  <li><span>1</span><div><strong>Open handle settings</strong><p>In Bluesky, go to <strong>Settings → Account → Handle</strong>.</p></div></li>
  <li><span>2</span><div><strong>Choose “I have my own domain”</strong><p>Continue with <strong>No DNS Panel</strong> to reveal your account DID.</p></div></li>
  <li><span>3</span><div><strong>Paste the DID below</strong><p>Neocities will publish the verification file for this site.</p></div></li>
</ol>

<form method="POST" action="/settings/<%= @site.username %>/bluesky_set_did" class="settings-form settings-form-card">
  <%== csrf_token_input_html %>
  <div class="settings-field">
    <label for="bluesky_did">Bluesky DID</label>
    <input id="bluesky_did" class="input-Area settings-mono-input" name="did" type="text" placeholder="did:plc:somethingexamplesomething" autocapitalize="off" autocorrect="off" spellcheck="false">
    <small>It begins with <code>did:plc:</code>.</small>
  </div>
  <div class="settings-actions">
    <input class="btn-Action" type="submit" value="Update DID">
  </div>
</form>